cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper presents a neural network architecture for object detection in autonomous driving scenarios using LIDAR point clouds and RGB images. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on autonomous driving, which suggests that it could belong to robotics (cs.RO). The proposed architecture uses deep learning techniques, which could place it in machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) to some extent, as it uses text to describe the proposed architecture, which could suggest a possible category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). However, given that NLP is not the main focus of the paper, it is less likely to belong to this category.
